          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            These terms apply to all users of ClipQwik, including beta testers and paid subscribers.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Beta Program Terms</h2>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">Experimental Nature</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            ClipQwik is currently in beta testing. The Plugin is provided on an experimental basis and may contain bugs, errors, or other issues. We make no guarantees about the Plugin's performance, reliability, or suitability for any particular purpose.
          </p>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">No Warranties</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            THE PLUGIN IS PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT.
          </p>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">Subject to Change</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            During the beta period, features, pricing, and functionality may change without notice. We reserve the right to modify or discontinue the Plugin at any time.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Plugin License</h2>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">License Grant</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Subject to your compliance with these Terms, we grant you a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable license to use ClipQwik in accordance with your subscription tier.
          </p>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">Subscription Tiers</h3>
          <div class="bg-gray-900 border border-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-4">
            <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3">
              <strong class="text-white">Free Tier:</strong>
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 leading-relaxed space-y-1 mb-4">
              <li>50 AI operations per month</li>
              <li>Basic timeline operations</li>
              <li>Community support</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3">
              <strong class="text-white">Pro Tier ($15/month or $120/year):</strong>
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 leading-relaxed space-y-1">
              <li>Unlimited AI operations</li>
              <li>Advanced Fusion generation</li>
              <li>Priority support</li>
              <li>Custom templates</li>
              <li>Local backend option</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">License Restrictions</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            You may not:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 leading-relaxed space-y-2">
            <li>Modify, reverse engineer, or decompile the Plugin</li>
            <li>Distribute, sublicense, or resell the Plugin</li>
            <li>Use the Plugin for unlawful purposes</li>
            <li>Share your account credentials with others</li>
            <li>Attempt to circumvent usage limits or payment systems</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">User Responsibilities</h2>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">System Requirements</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            ClipQwik requires DaVinci Resolve (Free or Studio) to be installed on your computer. You are responsible for ensuring your system meets all requirements to run both DaVinci Resolve and ClipQwik.
          </p>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">Proper Usage</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            You agree to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 leading-relaxed space-y-2">
            <li>Use the Plugin only for legitimate video editing purposes</li>
            <li>Maintain backups of your DaVinci Resolve projects before using the Plugin</li>
            <li>Not use the Plugin in ways that could harm or overload our services</li>
            <li>Comply with all applicable laws and regulations</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            ClipQwik, including all software, documentation, and related materials, is owned by Minim-l, LLC and is protected by copyright, trademark, and other intellectual property laws.
          </p>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">Your Content</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            You retain all rights to the video projects and content you create using ClipQwik. We do not claim any ownership over your creative work.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            <strong class="text-white">IMPORTANT:</strong> ClipQwik automates operations in DaVinci Resolve that modify your timeline and projects. While we strive for accuracy, we cannot guarantee that all operations will execute as expected.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-yellow-900/20 border border-yellow-600/30 rounded-lg p-6 mb-4">
            <p class="text-yellow-200 leading-relaxed mb-3">
              <strong class="text-yellow-100">⚠️ Critical Disclaimer:</strong>
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-yellow-200/90 leading-relaxed space-y-2">
              <li>Always maintain backups of your DaVinci Resolve projects</li>
              <li>Test operations on non-critical projects first</li>
              <li>We are not liable for any data loss or project corruption</li>
              <li>Use the Plugin at your own risk</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, MINIM-L, LLC SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, INCLUDING WITHOUT LIMITATION, LOSS OF PROFITS, DATA, USE, OR OTHER INTANGIBLE LOSSES, RESULTING FROM YOUR USE OF THE PLUGIN.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            IN NO EVENT SHALL OUR TOTAL LIABILITY EXCEED THE AMOUNT YOU PAID FOR THE PLUGIN IN THE TWELVE (12) MONTHS PRECEDING THE CLAIM.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Payment Terms</h2>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">Billing Cycle</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Pro tier subscriptions are billed monthly ($15/month) or annually ($120/year) based on your selection. Billing begins immediately upon subscription and recurs automatically until canceled.
          </p>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">Refund Policy</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Due to the digital nature of the Plugin and the beta status, all sales are final. However, we may provide refunds at our discretion on a case-by-case basis within 7 days of purchase.
          </p>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">Cancellation</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            You may cancel your subscription at any time. Upon cancellation, you will retain access to Pro features until the end of your current billing period. No refunds will be provided for partial billing periods.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Termination</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            We reserve the right to suspend or terminate your access to ClipQwik at any time, with or without notice, for any reason, including but not limited to violation of these Terms. Upon termination, your license to use the Plugin will immediately cease.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Governing Law</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the United States, without regard to its conflict of law provisions. Any disputes arising from these Terms or your use of the Plugin shall be resolved in the courts of competent jurisdiction.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Changes to Terms</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
            We may modify these Terms at any time. We will notify users of material changes by email (to the address provided during signup) or by posting a notice on our website. Your continued use of the Plugin after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Contact</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            If you have any questions about these Terms, please contact us:
          </p>
          <div class="bg-gray-900 border border-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
            <p class="text-gray-300 mb-2">
              <strong class="text-white">Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:support@clipqwik.com" class="text-purple-400 hover:text-purple-300">support@clipqwik.com</a>
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-300">
              <strong class="text-white">Company:</strong> Minim-l, LLC
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <div class="bg-gray-900 border border-purple-600/30 rounded-lg p-6">
            <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
              By using ClipQwik, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by these Terms and Conditions.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
